article.headline: Murray State 73, TCU 67
article.story: FORT WORTH, Texas (AP) -- Cuthbert Victor had a double-double with 17 points and 13 rebounds to lead Murray State to a 73-67 victory over TCU on Wednesday night. Kelvin Crown had 22 points and Rick Jones added 12 for Murray State (5-0). TCU (1-3) committed a season-high 19 turnovers but still led 38-32 at halftime after shooting 63 percent from the field. TCU went cold in the second half, going 9-of-30. Nucleus Smith scored 11 points and Chudi Chinweze added 10 for TCU, which is off to its worst start since the 1995-96 season.
